<title>USA: Pudgie's gets preliminary financing OK.</title>
<headline>Pudgie's gets preliminary financing OK.</headline>
<dateline>UNIONDALE, N.Y. 1997-03-04</dateline>
<text>
<p>Pudgie's Chicken Inc said on Tuesday that Bankruptcy Court gave preliminary approval of debtor-in-possession financing extended by a private source.</p>
<p>The court authorized Pudgie's to borrow a portion of the entire $250,000 secured loan facility on an interim basis and has scheduled a hearing for March 13, 1997 to consider final approval of the loan, Pudgie's said.</p>
<p>Jeffrey Zisselman, a private investor, is providing the financing, the company said.</p>
<p>Pudgie's filed Chapter 11 in September 1996.</p>
